      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, but when looking at the raw crime data itself, doesn't the data show that certain groups just commit more crime at higher rates regardless of their socioeconomic status? some people argue that the systemic stuff is just a cover for actual behavioral differences between groups.",
